This means that a call to:

{code}
ReviewService.getReviewsInStates(ReviewData.State.values(), false);
{code}

will never return any Snippets. Since - ReviewData.State uses:
{code}
 OpenSnippet,
 ClosedSnippet
{code}

and StateManager uses:
{code}

        State openSnippet = addState("Open Snippet", "Open", States.OPEN_SNIPPET_STATE, MetaState.OPEN);
        State closedSnippet = addState("Closed Snippet", "Closed", States.CLOSED_SNIPPET_STATE, MetaState.CLOSED);

{code}

ie. "Open Snippet" is stored in the database but OpenSnippet is what is used to retrieve it.


The following code snippet highlights this problem:
{code}
  List<ReviewData> reviews = service.getReviewService().getAllReviews(false); // get all reviews, except for DEAD ones
  List<ReviewData> reviewsInStates = service.getReviewService().getReviewsInStates(ReviewData.State.values(), false); // get all reviews, except for SNIPPETS
{code}

From a plugin-developer's point of view - that is utterly confusing.

